The paper deals with coding theory and its application to DNA-based storage systems, which suggests that it belongs to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the structure of unordered sequences and the task of placing them in their correct order, which relates to the Data Structures (cs.DS) and Data Mining (cs.DM) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the issue of errors in the index field, which is a topic in Cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a new family of codes that can correct errors and cluster the strands together, which relates to the Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
